  "text": "Phage content. Prophages are important drivers of diversity in S. enterica, and there is a high degree of diversity in the prophage content of different serovars of Salmonella, and even within serovars. For example, while S. Enteritidis P125109 and S. Enteritidis LK5 both contain five prophage regions, the actual prophages present in these two strains differ [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
